
This transaction represents the depreciation recorded on January 1, 2024, with an amount of 45757.71.

Looking through the remaining transactions, I don't see any other entries with type "Depreciation". This suggests that this is the only depreciation entry in the given time period.

Since depreciation is typically a periodic expense (recorded monthly, quarterly, or annually), and there's only one entry for the period covered by these transactions, the amount of 45757.71 represents the total depreciation expense for the income statement.
